<h1 style="text-align: center; margin-top: 180px;" class="display-3">Aim of comUNICEF</h1>
<p style="text-align: center" class="lead">This website was made during the 2017 Auckland University of Technology Hackathon, which was backed by UNICEF. The brief for the competition was to create an application, it being an app, game, website, or anything else that might aid UNICEF in any way. The participants were students from year 11 to 13, in groups of 4. We had 6 days to create this application during the Term 2 school holidays. Thanks to those who helped to host this event at AUT, and to UNICEF for supporting the event.
    <br>We opted for a website because we felt that it was by far the best medium for communication between people. We believe that one of the best things programming can bring to any group like UNICEF, with difficult and ongoing goals, is the creation of an easily accessible social environment that allows for the development of ideas, goals, and initiatives. This competition has taught us a lot about how much computer science can affect seemingly unrelated fields.
    <br>In the future, we would like to see this website used to it's fullest potential by schools, community groups, and organisations in order to raise awareness and to be proactive about UNICEF's mission. </p>

<script>
    var slideIndex = 1;
    showSlides(slideIndex);

    function plusSlides(n) {
        showSlides(slideIndex += n);
    }

    function currentSlide(n) {
        showSlides(slideIndex = n);
    }

    function showSlides(n) {
        var i;
        var slides = document.getElementsByClassName("mySlides");
        var dots = document.getElementsByClassName("dot");
        if (n > slides.length) {slideIndex = 1}
        if (n < 1) {slideIndex = slides.length}
        for (i = 0; i < slides.length; i++) {
            slides[i].style.display = "none";
        }
        for (i = 0; i < dots.length; i++) {
            dots[i].className = dots[i].className.replace(" active", "");
        }
        slides[slideIndex-1].style.display = "block";
        dots[slideIndex-1].className += " active";
    }
</script>




